// CLIAppGroup-Shared.xcconfig
// THE single derivation of the CLI/MCP App Group id — INV-4 in plans/cli-mcp.md.
//
// Both the GuessWho app target AND the guesswho-cli helper target #include the
// per-configuration variant of this file (CLIAppGroup-Debug.xcconfig /
// CLIAppGroup-Release.xcconfig), so within any single build the two processes
// always derive the SAME group string. Never hardcode this group anywhere —
// a hardcoded copy that drifts from this derivation is a silent IPC failure
// (app and helper resolve different containers; plan Phase 0, exit crit 3).
//
// Form: `<TeamID>.<parent-bundle-id>.cli<channel-suffix>` — the TeamID-prefixed
// (NOT `group.`-prefixed) App Group form, matching the app's existing Catalyst
// group (see GuessWho-Release.xcconfig): self-authorizing by code signature,
// no provisioning/portal registration, and no macOS 15+ consent prompt. The
// Muse reference derives `group.$(DEVELOPMENT_TEAM).$(PARENT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)`;
// GuessWho adapts the same structure to its documented TeamID-form convention.
//
// The channel suffix is what makes the string differ per channel. Muse gets
// this for free because its parent bundle id is itself channel-suffixed
// (museios-appstore / museios-setapp / museios-dev); GuessWho's Debug builds
// deliberately share the production bundle id (GuessWho-Debug.xcconfig), so
// the channel distinction is an explicit suffix component instead:
//   * Debug:               <team>.com.milestonemade.guesswho.cli.debug
//   * Release (App Store + TestFlight): <team>.com.milestonemade.guesswho.cli
//   * TODO(Setapp): when the Setapp channel is stood up (new configuration +
//     Developer ID signing — real, separate work; see plan Phase 0
//     "Channel-config prerequisite"), add CLIAppGroup-Setapp.xcconfig with
//     GUESSWHO_CLI_CHANNEL_SUFFIX = .setapp and re-run the Phase 0 exit
//     criteria on that channel.
//
// Runtime consumers (never a literal string):
//   * app:    GuessWhoCLIAppGroup Info.plist key (GuessWho/Info.plist)
//   * helper: GuessWhoCLIAppGroup key in its embedded Info.plist
//             (guesswho-cli/Info.plist, embedded via
//             CREATE_INFOPLIST_SECTION_IN_BINARY)
//   * both entitlements files reference $(GUESSWHO_CLI_APP_GROUP) directly.

GUESSWHO_CLI_PARENT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER = com.milestonemade.guesswho
GUESSWHO_CLI_APP_GROUP = $(DEVELOPMENT_TEAM).$(GUESSWHO_CLI_PARENT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER).cli$(GUESSWHO_CLI_CHANNEL_SUFFIX)
